<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I am very familiar with PvP combat as an enchnater and you will not win very often with fear or charm. You can increase your odds by ditching CHA for INT and might have enough mana to finish off a player, but then your screwed next time you need to mes/charm an NPC. Our DDs are slow and inefficient, and our DoTs rob us of our mes line. Whirl is broken by our pet bashing and all of our DDs, color flux can be very hard to use due to latency, and stunning your opponent for 3 seconds is not going to kill them (color flux is only slightly better than bash really). What I have decided to do, IF I continue to keep playing is to just kill people that are low on life and figthing something else that the time. See how Verant nerfs that.
</FONT>
