<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Well this post was not intended to say that all I ever did was charm someone and send them to their deaths (because I never did this).  But in a one on one battle we have only one shot to take down another caster.  If we get the first Sanity warp/Chaos Flux in, we should be able to alternate the two spells because of the brief stun to keep them from casting.  We will never have enough mana to take down a melee type.  Our pets are laughable compared to a true melee, and even if we were to lay down all of our debuffs they would be able to finish the pet and come for us.  The debuffs might slow them down enough for us to run away, but we'll never have the mana to beat them. <P>Charm was our big safety net, in that it did allow for us to send them against their own team, or just make them sit down while I made a break for it.  My main use of charm was to grab the Naked Mage and bring him to a set location.  Shout it out so that all the people he had been abusing could swarm him.  Of course being an a$$hole naked mage he'd show up again in 2 minutes blasting away again.  After doing this once, they usually would get the picture and leave.  If they kept coming I'd warn them that I would make them eat a giant.  I never had to do it.  But every single player that was waiting where I "pulled" my charmed victim was shouting "Send him to the guards"  "Send him to the Sand Giant" and I refused every time.<P>What a lot of you "experts" on PvP (and yet don't play on a PvP server) do not realize is Faction hits for PvP.  For any other class, faction hits are not as bad because you aren't required to go all over Norrath.  Guess what?  Enchanters do.  And the faction hits for killing another player are HUGE.  I know plenty of enchanters who could never make it into High Pass to buy their pet spells or do the Stein Quest 20 times because of faction.  Charm was the best way for me to avoid the faction hit because I could control the enemy until my friends could finish it.  Fear was the best protection for levels 4-11.  <P>There were bugs associated with these spells.  And little kids (and immature adults) abused spells like charm to ruin other peoples games.  But it still does not justify the removal of the spells from our arsenal.  It's not as if someone playing on the PvP servers didn't know that enchanters could charm.  I absolutely think that the bugs should have been fixed.  I would have been perfectly fine if they said charmed PC's can only attack other PC's.  But my point is that instead of taking the time to properly fix the problem, they took an easy way out and I am less effective because of it.<P><BR>Charm was my trump card that I held close to my chest.  It was the main defense against the PK vultures.  Now it has been snatched away.  Enchanters are still a great class for controlling the environment; we help a group in so many ways.  But if I am solo anywhere, I am a target now thanks to this nerf.  This won't affect the bug abusers and the pker's.  They'll find another class to exploit.  They ruined the fun of the enchanters who played fair and loved their class because of the support role we play.  <P>So please none of this, "You obviously don't understand how an Enchanter is played" nonsense.  There was a bug in these two spells, and those two spells happened to also be our best defence when used properly.  Verant chose to remove them rather than fix them.<P>Flame if you wish.  But try to justify it to a fair player who enjoyed the roleplaying aspects of PvP, rather than - "You're a d00d and you got what you desevered for sending thousands of newbies to their deaths."  
</FONT>
