<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
drexia hit it right on as far as the faction hits that we take in the pvp server.  i'm a level 37 enchanter on tallon zek(drexia one of these days we need to meet in the game=)  and of the 37 levels i've used charm less then 20 times(that includs pvp and regular hunting)  i dont like the randomness of the spell even though i'm a high elf enchanter with cha buffed to the hilt.  i have charmed my friends who fell asleep at the keyboard and sat them down at a safe spot more then i've used it in combat.  the only time i've used the spell in combat is to control those childish naked mage d00ds who wanted me dead over and over again.  sending them to the guards was the only way that i can tell them that i do not appreciate them being childish at my expense.  now i would actually have to kill them over and over again which will ruin my factions that i spent 37 levels protecting.  i am one of the few enchanter that i know on tallon zek that can still finish the tashania quest.(the other being drexia=)  unfortunately all of the enchanter's(that i know) on the "light" side that can cast clarity are starting new char.(most of them wizzy)  i personally started a erud wizzy so i can level faster.  what people do not understand, and that include alot of the enchanters, is that factions are everything to an enchanter.  we depend on it because no other class needs to go to the other side(neriak for the light side and high hold for the dark side) to get spells that we NEED.  i would like to see what pvp would be like if warriors (on the light side) need to buy crafted armor in oggok and they are no drop, or i would like to see druids go buy their "no drop" ensnare spell from neriak.  yes you can live without the "quests"  but dont make them impossible for enchanters just because it is pvp, after all this is still Ever"QUEST".  taking away the only thing that allows us to protect our factions is essentally taking out the quests for enchanters who chose to play enchanters because we are the ONLY class that can do the quests in a pvp environment.  <BR>now as for those who do not feel that we are STILL the king of pvp here are some hints:<BR>1. i can still mez mobs even when there are 2 of them beating on me so there is no way any class is going to prevent me from mezzing them. <BR>2. mezzing is alot more predictable then charm so you know the amount of time you have before they are going to break the mez.<BR>3. we are the only class with clarity.  medding for 30 seconds while they are mezed give you alot more mana then that erud wizzy with 200+ int.<BR>4. all of our dd spells have a built in stun(whether the spell is resisted or not the stun will still come through) which intrupt their 6 second cast time spells(ice comet)<BR>5. we have nullify magic, strip enchantment for those nasty dots or the 26 buffs that shamans have.<BR>6. remember we control what we want to fight.  if you dont want to fight then dont.  mez, sit down and mem gate if you dont have it memed then get out of there.  <P>so with those hints you should be able to take down any class you want because while you are medding for another nuke, they are mezzed and wandering why they are dumb enough to attack a class who can just park them there for 30 to 45 seconds while deciding what is the best way to kill them.  our mez takes way less mana then is recovered during a 30 second med with clarity so dont let those doom sayer tell you the wizzys have more mana then you.  the sheer fear that is driven into your foe by mezzing them is enough to scare them away 95% of the time.  even if you are a newbie/lowbie and cant afford to sit down and med for long before they break the mez, the fact that you are sitting down right in front of them and medding tells them that they are out classed. besides if you are really good you can start to mess with their head when their mezed and just say things like "let's see, how would you like to die today? would you like me to charm that griffon to kill you or would you like me to just nuke you to death?  wait i forgot to mem charm, let me mem that first just in case i decided that is the way i want to kill you"  that will tell them that they messed with the wrong class and need to find a new pair of underwear.  warriors are mezed just as well as casters nobody is immune to mez and it will come through for you most of the time.  if you are dealing with a pet class, it only means that you have to mez twice instead of once it is the same game over and over again.  people think that charm was our only weapon in pvp and it is simply not true.  of the enchanters that actually made it pass level 25 know that charm is about the last spell you want to depend on during combat because if it breaks early, they are dead because it is intrupt city after that.  so enchanters that know how to play enchanter rely on mez instead of charm so they really didnt lose much as far as combat effectiveness.  only thing that we lost due to the nerf was our ability to defend our factions.  without factions there can be no tashania, without tashania there can be no effective fear/hate raids=(  so why level up when you know that you cant be all that you can be when the other classes are able to get their best items/spells.  for those who have depended on charm for pvp i feel sorry for you.  as an enchanter you should have avoided pvp when possible and if you didnt your factions are already gone which you didnt really lose anything. now you just have to learn how to play an enchanter the right way and not whine about it.  for those of you who have been protecting your factions, i'm in the same boat you are in.  i chose to start a new char but that doesnt mean i'm gonna ditch this one completely.  be extra careful because they are hunting us now just because of the few who didnt know better.  now like drexia said mez and get out of there.  have a few places that you hunt so you can leave one zone for a few hours while the childish ones get put to bed then you can go back to hunt that zone.  we are still the best pvp class but we still cant afford to pvp=(  just take it with a grain of salt and remember everquest life goes on=)<BR>
