First off, I never professed to be an expert... I play on a PvP server and last I heard they removed the faction hit system from it.  Second off, I rarely attack another player- allies are better than enemies, murderers are best left to flattery on their cowardly kills to keep them from doing it again.<P>But some points to make:<P>1) We have a very fast 0 range AE spell series that stuns those about us... sometimes briefly, longer at higher levels.  Gives us time to cast more spells.<P>2) Not only do we have mesmerize we have mesmerization... a single target and AE 30 second stun, and if I recall stronger versions of these exist to leave them sitting longer.<P>3) We can med while they sit there useless, and you can switch spells while medding...<P>4) Non-damage spells- ie our many Debuffs we carrry- will not break this mesmerzation...<P>5) If we want a pet to command vs our poor animation and are willing to risk its variable duration, we can still use charm on NPCs...<P>Please, think about all our capabilities - an enchanter's fulcrum on PvP was never the ability to charm his opponent but to use various enchantments and disenchantments to overpower them.<P>Our DDs do stun, our DOTS sap str/dex, we have str debuffs, str/dex debuffs, attack speed debuffs, don't know if the strip enchantment line works anymore on PvP after the cancel magic fiasco...<P>My only point is we still do what were meant to do.  Can't take on a warrior?  When the melee type is reduced to the strength of an infant, has his attack speed reduced, his dex is drained, and his armor heavily encumbers him reducing agi/movement then I think our "wimpy" pets with AC, Str, and attack speed buffs do quite well against even them...  can't take on spellcasters?  When we can mesmerize, blast, mez, med, blast (and so on) I think we get a bit of an edge... even without clarity!<P>But, in the end, EQ was never meant to have one class be able to dominate the game solo... after all, which would you rather face 3 PKing enchanters or a group of 1 enchanter (buffs/debuffs), 1 druid (movement/tport/heals), and 1 ranger (track,melee)?  As far as soloing though, we still rock.. just always keep color shift type spells and a mesmerize up... that will let you stun your foes long enough to med up the spells you need to PK.<P>------------------<BR>Kithra Of Rallos Zek<BR>Enchanter and Craftsman<BR>of Freeport
