what is all this idiocy, hello?  can we get some critical thinking here, PLEASE?<P>first off, any one who does not play on a pvp server, SHUT UP NOW.  you have absolutely NO clue what youre talking about, so dont bother<P>second, unless you have used a strategy MULTIPLE times in an EVEN or OUTMATCHED situation, dont bother telling me about it<P>ok, id say i just weeded out about 90% of you.  for the rest of you, you already know what im about to say, but here goes...<P>think about how much damage our spells do...  our dds are dead last on casting time, the WORST for mana efficiency, and dont do NEARLY enough damage to make up for those two shortcommings (talking about pvp, so settle down all you smurfs--for the mentally challenged, smurf = blue).<P>second, our dots hardly do any damage to begin with, and when a player is moving around (which they nearly ALWAYS are in pvp) they take a fraction of the normal damage<P>with those two facts, you will soon realize (or just by going out and having your ass handed to you multiple times) that enchanters barely have enough mana to kill an equal lvl CASTER, let alone a TANK!  you will not, i repeat WILL NOT have enough mana, to do enough damage, to kill a tank from full (or anywhere in the same zip code as full) health.  period.<P>but, our kind theorhetically thinking friends will tell us that our fully buffed pet, fully buffed self, will be able to kill that fully debuffed tank just fine.  awesome!  you play the tank and patiently wait while i repeatedly med and cast so that i CAN cast all those buff/debuff spells!  what you all are forgetting is, you need MANA AND TIME TO CAST ALL THOSE SPELLS, not to mention spell slots!  by the time you mez and remem spells enough times to even go through all those spells, you will be OUT OF MANA.  i take that back, you wont even HAVE enough mana to mez/cast/med through all your buff/debuff spells, and that says NOTHING about damage spells.<P>REALITY CHECK:  YOU...DO...NOT...HAVE...THAT...MUCH...MANA!<P>of course, that last statement completely ignores such trivial things as time.  by the time you finish casting all your lovely enchantments, the first ones will be beginning to wear off.  and what if some other player wanders along while youre fighting?  whos side are they going to take?  they could just as easily figure that you are LOM (gee, they would guess right, wouldnt they?) and try to take you down as an easy kill.  or what if a mob ambles by (you know, those things that give you xp when you kill em?)?  do you suppose mr mob is going to smile and wave?  as an interesting side-bar, did you know that NON-agro mobs will AGRO on pcs that are fighting?  is it not nifty?<P>and another thing to remember, if you are using a pet (like was sooo helpfully suggested), that completely REMOVES MEZ as an option.  no sooner is the pc mezd, then the pet hits them and they come after you again.<P>so there you go.  in practical use for pvp, enchanters are worthless.<P>if you want to play pvp, you have very limited choices:<BR>wizard<BR>mage<BR>necro<BR>druid<BR>shaman<P>------------------<BR>"evil will always triumph over good, because good ... is dumb"
