<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I play on Tallon Zek, and have read all the posts about the nerfs to enchanters. Thought I'd say a few things as well.<P>I have been in solo fights, and been in group pvp battles quite a few times.<P>Hands down the group battles were more fun because you could charm an enemy tank (monk or fighter preferred) and have them attack their friends. I did this a few times in big battles and it was a blast.  Of course I was also around level 14 at the time and during that range of levels (1-20) is when a lot of pvp takes place.<P>Now, of course the enchanter can't do that anymore. They CAN charm an npc to attack, but there are some problems with that. An NPC when it breaks charm will track you down 100% of the time and make your life hell if it is anywhere close to your level. On the other hand, charming a player meant that once the charm broke, they couldn't track you down and didn't even know who charmed them (if it was a big battle).<P>Now for solo pvp, I've had the following happen. I was attacked. I had no pet, so I mesmerized my opponent, sat down medded to full, then proceeded to blast with DD (chaos flux) then remeze and sit to med. I killed my opponent.<P>Now I was attacked with my pet once, and that makes it much harder. I can't mesmerize because the pet would break it immediately. So I ran.  I didn't have the proper spells memmed for pvp (I was camping for xp), but I got lucky and far enough away, plus my opponent had snared my pet so I could now mez him. Since he was red to me I sat down and memmed gate, and gated away. I could not have killed him since he was 3-4 levels higher and a druid/ranger.<P>In my small group experience, I and two other enchanters mopped the floor with guys who were 2-3 levels higher than us.  We all had pets. We had our roles, I cast EoC to keep them blinded and whirled. My friends blasted with DD. We wasted the opponents who had one pet, so it was 6 to 4 (us 3 with 3 pets, them 3 with 1 pet). Never underestimate a pet, even an enchanters weak ones (they were not buffed in any way either).<P>I would like to have charm and fear back, as it was a good tool set to have in PvP, but I dont want them back if they are broken, I want them fixed. The Tuning Team was still wrong to just yank those spells without saying they were going to fix them and return them at some point.<P>All in all I like playing my enchanter, though I have been tempted to make another class with the nerfs going on. Of course necros got hit hard with the fear spell taken out of pvp too.<P>Guess what I'm trying to say is the enchanter class is still good at pvp, and really good in a group. But I'd like charm and fear back fixed so they can't be abused like they were.
</FONT>
